## Combining Futures

```java
// Run two tasks in parallel and combine results
CompletableFuture<User> userFuture = fetchUser(id);
CompletableFuture<List<Order>> orderFuture = fetchOrders(id);

CompletableFuture<UserProfile> profile = userFuture
    .thenCombine(orderFuture, (user, orders) -> 
        new UserProfile(user, orders));

// Wait for ALL of N futures
CompletableFuture<Void> all = CompletableFuture.allOf(
    future1, future2, future3);

// Collect results
List<String> results = Stream.of(future1, future2, future3)
    .map(CompletableFuture::join)
    .collect(Collectors.toList());
```

## Custom Thread Pool

By default, `CompletableFuture` uses the common `ForkJoinPool`. For I/O-heavy operations, use a dedicated thread pool:

```java
Executor ioPool = Executors.newFixedThreadPool(50);

CompletableFuture.supplyAsync(() -> httpCall(), ioPool)
    .thenApplyAsync(result -> transform(result), ioPool);
```

## Error Handling

```java
future
    .thenApply(this::riskyOp)
    .exceptionally(ex -> defaultValue)       // recover from error
    .handle((result, ex) -> {                // handle both cases
        if (ex != null) return fallback;
        return result;
    });
```
